Professor Brian Armstrong, chair of digital business at Wits Business School and former Telkom COO, will deliver the keynote address at the 2019 MyBroadband Fibre Conference. The 2019 MyBroadband Fibre Conference will take place on Wednesday 17 July at The Venue in Houghton and will feature top industry experts as speakers. Delegates will also hear from SEACOM CSO Suveer Ramdhani, Octotel CEO Rob Gilmour, DFA’s Vino Govender, CipherWave MD Wayne D’SA, and MTN’s Calvin Govender. These speakers will cover a wide range of topics, including fibre network rollouts in SA, FTTH and FTTB from an ISP’s perspective, fibre versus 5G, and national and international fibre networks. Tickets for the 2019 Fibre Conference are still available at a discount using the promotional code below. Many top fibre companies have partnered with MyBroadband for the 2019 Fibre Conference, including DFA, Dartcom, Broadband Infraco, MetroFibre, MiRO, Even Flow, and Angola Cables. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-313055" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Fibre-Conference-Sponsors.jpg" alt="Fibre Conference Sponsors" width="640" height="1448" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Fibre-Conference-Sponsors.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Fibre-Conference-Sponsors-177x400.jpg 177w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Fibre-Conference-Sponsors-190x430.jpg 190w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" />